{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:08:25.485Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scaling"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Normalization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are essential data preprocessing techniques that transform numerical features to a common scale so that no single feature dominates the model due to its larger magnitude — they ensure fair comparisons between features and enable faster, more stable training for many machine learning algorithms."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What They Are: The Core Problem"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Common challenge"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\nFeatures in datasets rarely live on the same scale:\n- Some variables are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "counts"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (e.g., number of purchases: 0–100)\n- Others are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "percentages"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (e.g., interest rate: 0–100%)\n- Others are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "monetary values"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (e.g., annual income: $0–$1,000,000)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "If you feed them directly into a model"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Results can be misleading\n- Features with larger values dominate\n- Model performance degrades"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scaling: Transforming to Common Range"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Definition"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": The process of transforming numerical features to a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "common range or scale"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Purpose"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Ensures no single feature dominates the learning process due to larger magnitude."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Scaling & Normalization — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Min-Max Scaling (Normalization)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it does"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Scales data to a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "fixed interval"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", typically "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "italic"}, {"type": "italic"}], "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$\\text{X}"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{new}} = \\frac{x - \\min(x)}{\\max(x) - \\min(x)}$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = original value\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\min(x)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = minimum value of feature\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\max(x)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = maximum value of feature"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What happens"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Subtract minimum value\n- Divide by range (max − min)\n- Preserves "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "shape o